commText: Warner and Prithvi Shaw are at the crease. Warner is on strike. Starc will open the attack
Starc to Warner, 1 run, short of length outside off, Warner leaps and steers it to the left of third man
Starc to Prithvi Shaw, no run, I0$ full outside off, Prithvi Shaw opens the bat face and pushes it into the covers
Starc to Prithvi Shaw, no run, shortens the length and keeps it outside off, Prithvi Shaw punches it into the covers
Starc to Prithvi Shaw, 2 runs, I0$ length delivery angled in on middle and leg, Prithvi Shaw flicks and gets it off the thick inside half in the gap between mid-on and mid-wicket
Starc to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, I0$ short and wide of off, Prithvi Shaw slaps the cut and slices it off thick outside edge to the left of the fielder at third man
Starc to Prithvi Shaw, FOUR, short and wide of off, Prithvi Shaw gets up on his toes and smashes it up and over covers with an air of disdain...
Here's the impact sub Vaibhav Arora. One slip in place for him...
Vaibhav Arora, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Warner, FOUR, that's a freebie and Warner doesn't miss out. Short and angled down leg, Warner swivels and helps it away to the fine leg fence with a pull

Vaibhav Arora to Warner, FOUR, thick top-edge but it goes away to the fence. I0$ short and angled into the ribcage, Warner took his eyes off trying to pull and the edge flies over Narine at short fine. One bounce and trickles away over the ropes...
Vaibhav Arora to Warner, wide, goes a bit fuller and bowls it well wide of off, Warner swings and misses
Vaibhav Arora to Warner, 1 run, I0$ full on off, Warner flicks off the cue end to the left of mid-wicket for a quick single
Huge cry for lbw

Vaibhav Arora to Prithvi Shaw, no run, Huge cry for lbw and KKR decide against the review or have they? Nope. They review with 3 seconds to go on the DRS timer. It's missed the bat confirms UltraEdge. Missing leg (going well over) according to ball tracker and it will remain not out. The inswinger from Vaibhav Arora and Prithvi Shaw played all around it looking to work leg-side, missed the inside edge and got hit on the pad in front of middle stump, the bounce eventually saved him...
Prithvi Shaw out caught? Has Varun taken it cleanly. The fingers are underneath says Kumar Dharamsena and that will do...
Vaibhav Arora to Prithvi Shaw, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Chakaravarthy!! Another in-ducker from Vaibhav Arora and Prithvi Shaw's attempted heave finds the thick inside edge. It flies low to the left of mid-on where Varun Chakaravarthy dives full length to grab an excellent catch inches above the turf. Managed to get his fingers under the ball and was in firm control of the catch as well. Knew he got it clean straightaway and started celebrating instantly. Prithvi Shaw c Chakaravarthy b Vaibhav Arora 10(7) [4s-2]
Mitchell Marsh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Vaibhav Arora to Mitchell Marsh, no run, back of a length outside off, Mitchell Marsh cuts it late to the left of backward point
Starc to Warner, leg byes, FOUR, full and angling down leg, Warner looks to flick and misses. It deflects off the pads and Mitchell Starc's pace takes care of the rest...
Starc to Warner, no run, drags the length back and keeps it wide of off, Warner swings and misses
Starc to Warner, no run, full and hint of inswing outside off, Warner toe-ends the drive to cover
Starc to Warner, 1 run, good length just outside off, Warner nudges it to the left of short mid-wicket for a quick single
Starc to Mitchell Marsh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Starc to Mitchell Marsh, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh !! Mitchell gets Mitchell. It's the 1st wicket for Starc in IPL 2024. Bowls it full and wide of off, Marsh senses an opportunity to free his arms and goes hard on the drive. End result? Slices it straight into the hands of Ramandeep Singh at backward point. This is also the first wicket for Starc in 59 balls this season. Mitchell Marsh c Ramandeep Singh b Starc 0(2)
Abishek Porel, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Abishek Porel, no run, swings away late outside off, Abishek Porel pokes and gets beaten on the outside edge
Marsh vs LA pace this IPL 37 runs, 20 balls, 3 dismissals
Vaibhav Arora to Warner, no run, I0$ swings away from a length outside off, lures Warner into a flat-footed push and beats the outside edge
Vaibhav Arora to Warner, 1 run, I0$ full and wide of off, Warner squeezes it with an open bat face to the right of third man

Vaibhav Arora to Abishek Porel, no run, fuller on the pads, Abishek Porel flicks but finds the fielder at mid-wicket. Direct hit at the bowling end and Warner managed to get back in the nick of time...
Vaibhav Arora to Abishek Porel, no run, I0$ length outside off, punched away to the right of cover
Vaibhav Arora to Abishek Porel, no run, full outside off, Abishek Porel toe-ends the drive back to the bowler
Vaibhav Arora to Abishek Porel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Abishek Porel, out Caught by Narine!! No impact from DC's impact sub unfortunately. He gets an excellent short ball from Vaibhav Arora - had nowhere to hide - and gets hurried on the pull. Flies high off the top-edge and Narine accepts the dolly at short fine. DC are in huge trouble now. Abishek Porel c Narine b Vaibhav Arora 0(5)
Rishabh Pant, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Warner, no run, I0$ length outside off, Warner cuts and finds cover
Starc to Warner, SIX, I0$ full outside off, Warner clears his front leg and smokes Starc into the mid-wicket stands for an 85-metre maximum
Most sixes in IPL while chasing 156 - Chris Gayle 113 - David Warner* 112 - Rohit Sharma 110 - Robin Uthappa 110 - Shane Watson
Starc to Warner, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Starc to Warner, out Bowled!! Chopped on. Starc gets his countryman. Shortens the length, slows the pace and keeps it outside off. Warner wanted to stab it on the off-side but instead got a thick inside edge that deflected to smash the middle of middle peg. 4 down are the Delhi Capitals and their dug-out pose a sorry look as Warner trudges back to the pavilion. Warner b Starc 18(13) [4s-2 6s-1]
Tristan Stubbs, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Tristan Stubbs, no run, short of length on off, Tristan Stubbs works it into the leg-side
Starc to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, I0$ low full toss outside off, Tristan Stubbs drives straight and gets it past the diving right hand of mid-off for a quick single
Starc to Pant, SIX, that was asking to be dispated and Pant just helped it on its path. I0$ full and angling down leg, Pant flicks and the timing takes it all the way over fine leg
Vaibhav Arora to Tristan Stubbs, no run, I0$ short of length outside off, Tristan Stubbs drags it to the right of mid-wicket
Mitchell Starc's bowling in PP this IPL Overs: 7 Runs: 71 Wkts: 2 ER: 10.14
Vaibhav Arora to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, seam-up length delivery just outside off, Tristan Stubbs opens the bat face really late and cuts to the left of backward point
Vaibhav Arora to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, Tristan Stubbs advances and goes through with the pull, thick top-edge and it flies away over short fine for a boundary
Vaibhav Arora to Tristan Stubbs, no run, gets the yorker right just outside off, Stubbs jams it back to the bowler
Vaibhav Arora to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, I0$ short outside off, Stubbs pulls to the right of mid-wicket and hares across for a quick single
Vaibhav Arora to Pant, wide, bumper outside off, Pant lets it pass. Too high and Vaibhav Arora will have to reload that...
Vaibhav Arora to Pant, 1 run, I0$ fuller on leg stump, clipped away to deep square
Powerplay scores for DC this IPL 1/54 vs PBKS 2/59 vs RR 0/62 vs CSK 4/51 vs KKR
Harshit Rana has gone off the field, not sure what the reason is. He was ready to bowl before that.
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Over Summary (1-6 ov) * Shaw gets going with a couple of boundaries * Warner gets going with a couple of boundaries * Shaw survives a close LBW review, but holes out to mid-on next ball * 1st IPL wicket for Starc, Mitch Marsh OUT for 0 * Porel falls for a 5-ball duck * Second wicket for Starc as Warner chops one back onto his stumps
Russell to Pant, 1 run, fuller length ball around off, Pant eases it through covers
Russell to Tristan Stubbs, no run, back of a length ball on off, Tristan Stubbs guides it to backward point
Russell to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, good length ball around off, Tristan Stubbs taps it past backward point to rotate strike

Russell to Pant, SIX, going, going, and gone! An off-cutter on a fuller length, Pant heaves it towards deep square leg. The fielder is interested for a while but he can only see it sailing over him and the fence

Russell to Pant, SIX, Pant is getting into the groove! A short ball on off, Pant was waiting for it. He stands tall and pulls it towards deep square leg. Not off the meat of the bat but has enough to clear the fielder
Russell to Pant, no run, this short ball is well-directed as it angles away. Pant arches back and drops his wrists to let it through
Time for Narine to roll his arm over. Can he shine with the ball too?
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Narine to Tristan Stubbs, no run, on a fuller length on off, Tristan Stubbs leans ahead and blocks it towards short mid-wicket
Narine to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, turning in from a back of a length on off, Tristan Stubbs camps back and works it to deep mid-wicket
Narine to Pant, 1 run, loopy full ball outside off, Pant crouches in his stance and fetches the sweep to get it towards deep backward square leg
Narine to Tristan Stubbs, leg byes, 1 run, on a length, turning in from outside off, Tristan Stubbs looks to reverse sweep but it goes off his thigh pad towards short third for a leg bye
Narine to Pant, 2 runs, on a flatter trajectory, Pant works it to the right of deep mid-wicket and returns for a brace.
Narine to Pant, no run, probing off-stump channel this time, Pant chops it besides him on the off-side. Looks for a run but it's not on
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, that made a cracking sound off the bat! Right in the slot for Tristan Stubbs to free his arms. He kneels down and clubs it over cow corner for a maximum
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, no run, on a back of a length and turning in to cramp Tristan Stubbs for room. He can only push it back to the bowler

Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, what a shot! Not easy to play such a shot off a spinner. On a back of a length in line of the stumps, Tristan Stubbs flat-bats it straight as an arrow with brute force

Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, dropped! Shorter in length, Tristan Stubbs mistimes the pull towards deep mid-wicket. It's dipping on Iyer who moves to his right. He gets both hands to it but can't hold on. Was quite a simple chance by Iyer's standards
Chakaravarthy to Pant, no run, full ball on off, Pant uses his feet and goes for the reverse hit but is struck on the arm
Chakaravarthy to Pant, no run, full ball outside off, Pant looks for the reverse sweep but is struck on the arm

Time for the strategic break! The scoreboard pressure has got the better of DC so far. Starc and Vaibhav Arora combined in unison to take four wickets within the powerplay. There's firepower in the form of Pant & Stubbs but they still have a long long way to go...
Narine to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, floated delivery outside off, stroked down to long-off
Narine to Pant, no run, on a flatter trajectory on off, cramping Pant for room. Pant was looking to cut through point but can only get it off the outer half past the keeper

Narine to Pant, no run, tossed up full ball on off, Pant looks to sweep it hard but looks like he got it off the back of his bat towards short third. Oh, actually the inside edge lobbed off onto his helmet. A mandatory concussion check for Pant and he is fine
Narine to Pant, no run, on a length around off, Pant chops it straight towards point
Narine to Pant, 1 run, Pant uses his feet and Narine smartly bowls it on a length around leg-stump. He can only tuck it trhough mid-wicket

Narine to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, shorter in length on off, Tristan Stubbs pulls it hard through mid-wicket. Venkatesh Iyer in the deep moves to his right and slides to cut it off. Another tidy over from Narine
Chakaravarthy to Pant, 1 run, coming in with the arm from a back of a length outside off, Pant works it to deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, back to over the wicket to the right-hander. On the shorter side, Tristan Stubbs flat-bats it and it goes on the bounce to long-on
Chakaravarthy to Pant, 1 run, bowls this one wider of Pant. He reaches out to it and flat-bats it past the bowler towards long-off
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, wide, this one is on a back of a length and wide outside off, cuts the tramline and wided
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, fired right into the blockhole around leg-stump, Tristan Stubbs can only jam it towards long-on
Chakaravarthy to Pant, 1 run, full ball on middle and leg, Pant whips it to the left of deep backward square leg
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, shot! A full in-drifter, Tristan Stubbs clears his front leg and powers it down the ground. Russell at long-on moves to his left and dives but it goes in vain
Live visuals show that Harshit Rana is sitting in the dressing room with an ice pack on his right shoulder
Venkatesh Iyer, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Venkatesh Iyer to Pant, FOUR, a freebie down the leg-side, Pant crouches in his stance and hits it over short fine to find the fence. Was a poor ball and got the treatment

Venkatesh Iyer to Pant, SIX, boom goes Pant! DC need to capitalize on the part-timer's over. A back of a length ball around off, Pant stands tall and hammers it over wide long-off for a maximum. Such power on that shot

Venkatesh Iyer to Pant, SIX, Pant is now toying with Venkatesh Iyer! A poor ball down leg to be honest, but Pant's audacity makes this shot exciting. He flicks/scoops it over short fine with an air of authority...
Venkatesh Iyer to Pant, FOUR, a gentle full-toss around off, Pant opens his bat-face and square drives it through backward point. Beats the fielder in the deep to his right with ease
Deep backward square leg comes in

Venkatesh Iyer to Pant, FOUR, fifty up for Pant! Consecutives fifiies for him! He has come back from injury and hasn't taken much time to return to his usual self. Fullish ball outside off, Pant whips it behind square on the leg-side for a boundary. He raises his bat and soaks in all the applause
Venkatesh Iyer to Pant, FOUR, 28 off the over! A full-toss outside off, Pant picks his spot to perfection again and carves it wide of deep backward point to find the fence again
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, tossed up delivery, Tristan Stubbs mistimes the heave but it goes on the bounce to deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Pant, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Pant, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! Pant's entertaining knock comes to an end! Chakaravarthy bowls this one on a fuller length wide outside off. Pant has to reach out to it. Perhaps not the right shot selection to go for the slog sweep but he goes for it. Ends up skewing it off the outer half of the bat over covers. Shreyas Iyer calls for it and takes a smart catch. Pant c Shreyas Iyer b Chakaravarthy 55(25) [4s-4 6s-5]
Axar Patel, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Axar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Axar, out Caught by (sub)Manish Pandey at straight down the ground!! Two wickets in two balls for Chakaravarthy! Brilliant take from Manish Pandey. Tossed up delivery around off, Axar goes for a big hit straightaway and toe-ends it towards long-on. Manish Pandey, the substitute fielder, runs in. There's another fielder in his vicinity running in from mid-wicket but he stays calm. Gets low, takes the catch with both hand, and then falls down on the ground. Axar c (sub)Manish Pandey b Chakaravarthy 0(1)
Sumit Kumar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Sumit Kumar, wide, on a length on middle, turning down, wided. Chakaravarthy is still on a hat-trick

Chakaravarthy to Sumit Kumar, no run, KKRR review for an lbw! Looked lik going down leg in real time. Was a length ball that turned in sharply from off, Sumit Kumar leant ahead to block but missed to get pinged on the front pad. Time for the replays. Ball-tracking comes into the picture and reveals it be going down leg
Chakaravarthy to Sumit Kumar, 1 run, floated on off, hit down to long-off
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, on the shorter side outside off, slapped to sweeper cover to retain strike
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Narine to Tristan Stubbs, no run, slow through the air and on off, Tristan Stubbs looks to sweep but gets it off the toe-end down the track

Narine to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, brute power on display from Tristan Stubbs once again! This one turns the other way, Tristan Stubbs rocks back, reads it perfectly, and powers it over extra cover for a maximum
Narine to Tristan Stubbs, SIX, in the arc, out of the park! In-drifter this time, Tristan Stubbs kneels down on on knee and heaves it over deep square leg for a biggie
Narine to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, tossed up delivery, hit down towards long-on
Most 50-plus scores for DC in IPL 24 - David Warner* 18 - Rishabh Pant* 18 - Shikhar Dhawan 16 - Shreyas Iyer 16 - Virender Sehwag 13 - Prithvi Shaw
Narine to Sumit Kumar, no run, quicker and flatter on off, Sumit Kumar gloves it besides the pitch on the leg-side
Narine to Sumit Kumar, SIX, a short delivery that sits up nicely for Sumit Kumar. He stands tall and hammers the pull over cow corner for a flat maximum

Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, fifty for Tristan Stubbs! The match might have gone out of hand but Stubbs is showing what a dangerous power-hitter he is. Tossed up delivery, stroked down to long-on. No celebration from the big South African
Chakaravarthy to Sumit Kumar, leg byes, 1 run, Sumit Kumar looks to work this one to the leg-side but it deflects off his pads towards short fine for a leg bye

Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, no ball, byes, FOUR, oh no, that one hasn't pitched on the pitch only. So wide outside off, leaves Philip Salt no chance to stop it and the ball races to the fence behind. No ball called by the umpire
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, no run, bowls this one in the blockhole this time, Tristan Stubbs can only dig it out
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, FOUR, tossed up outside off, Tristan Stubbs lines it up and smashes it over extra cover for a rocketing boundary
Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, out Caught by Starc!! Tristan Stubbs falls against the run of play! Chakaravarthy looks up the heavens and thanks his stars. Was a length ball drifting down leg, Tristan Stubbs mistimed his expansive stroke towards deep backward square leg. Starc took a few steps in and didn't make any mistake. Tristan Stubbs c Starc b Chakaravarthy 54(32) [4s-4 6s-4]
Rasikh Dar Salam, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Chakaravarthy to Rasikh Salam, no run, a chirpy appeal for an lbw! Was the quicker one on leg-stump, Rasikh Salam looked to counter it from the crease but was pinged on the pads. Might have gone down leg

Over Summary (7-15 ov) * Pant keeps attacking with two consecutive sixes off Russell * Stubbs joins the party with a couple of sixes off Chakaravarthy * Stubbs dropped by Shreyas Iyer off Chakaravarthy on 24 * Pant smashes Venkatesh Iyer for 28 runs in the 12th over, brings up his fifty in the process * Pant falls for a 25-ball 55, Chakaravarthy with the wicket * Axar Patel falls for a first-ball duck * A 28-ball half-century for Tristan Stubbs * Stubbs falls for a 32-ball 54, 3rd wicket for Chakaravarthy
Narine to Sumit Kumar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Narine to Sumit Kumar, out Caught by (sub)Manish Pandey!! Wickets falling in clusters now! Tossed up delivery on a length, Sumit Kumar looks to heave it over deep mid-wicket but doesn't get proper elevation and power behind the shot. Manish Pandey, the substitute, is safe as houses. Sumit Kumar c (sub)Manish Pandey b Narine 7(6) [6s-1]
Time for the strategic break! The writing is on the wall for DC. It will serve them well if they score some runs in the backend to not worsen their net run-rate
Anrich Nortje, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Nortje, no run, turning in from a length, Nortje looks to flick and is struck on the pads
A slip in place
Narine to Nortje, 1 run, floated delivery around off, driven to sweeper cover
Narine to Rasikh Salam, no run, 96.5kph slider on middle and leg, Rasikh Salam moves inside the line to sweep and only manages to glove it towards short fine
Narine to Rasikh Salam, no run, full ball outside off, Rasikh Salam leans into it and strokes it to extra cover
Narine to Rasikh Salam, 1 run, turning in from a back of a length, tucked to deep mid-wicket to retain strike. Narine bowls out with decent figures to cap off an excellent night
A false start for Arora in his new spell
Vaibhav Arora [3.0-0-22-2] is back into the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Rasikh Salam, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Rasikh Salam, out Caught by Philip Salt!! The short ball pays dividends to Vaibhav Arora once again! He has looked impressive tonight. He bowls a well-directed bouncer which gets big on Rasikh Salam. He is rushed on the pull and top-edges it to Philip Salt's right. The keeper takes it with ease. Rasikh Salam c Philip Salt b Vaibhav Arora 1(5)
Ishant Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Vaibhav Arora to Ishant, no run, skiddy back of a length ball around off, Ishant looks to punch it through covers and misses
Vaibhav Arora to Ishant, no run, a yorker length ball on off, Ishant digs it out to the off-side

Vaibhav Arora to Ishant, 1 run, Ishant backs away and Vaibhav Arora tucks him up with a short ball. Ishant fends it awkardly besides him on the leg-side and the batters take off. The throw deflects off Ishant and rolls towards long-on but they don't take the second
Vaibhav Arora to Nortje, wide, short ball around off, Nortje looks to pull but only meets thin air
Vaibhav Arora to Nortje, 2 runs, shortish ball outside off, Nortje slashes at it and it flies off an outside edge towards third man's left. A couple results
Vaibhav Arora to Nortje, 1 run, another shortish delivery, Nortje backs away and mistimes his flat-batted stroke towards mid-off
Andre Russell [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Russell to Nortje, no run, almost knocked him over! A slower back of a length ball on leg-stump, Nortje swings across the line and misses. The ball almost kisses the leg-stump
Russell to Nortje, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Nortje, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! That's the game! This is a massive, massive victory for KKR!! Ian Bishop on air mentions that it's the first time in the history of IPL that KKR have won their first three matches of the season on the trot. A back of a length delivery, Nortje backs away and mistimes his flat-batted stroke to mid-on and holes out to Shreyas Iyer. Beaming smiles in the KKR camp. This has been a proper drubbing. Nortje c Shreyas Iyer b Russell 4(6)

23:21 Local Time, 17:51 GMT, 23:21 IST: KKR continue to fly high - a complete all-round performance from the men in purple and gold! Shreyas Iyer elected to bat first on a proper highway of a track and his batters repaid the faith he had in them. Records were broken in galore as the visitors completely bossed the proceedings. Narine's free-flowing batting, young Raghuvanshi's classy knock, and quickfire cameos from Russell and Rinku Singh enabled KKR to post their highest score ever. It was always going to be an uphill task for DC and they were found wanting within the powerplay itself. They were reduced to 33/4 and from then on, the writing was on the wall for them. Pant and Stubbs lit up the stadium with their attractive strokeplay and stitched a 93-run stand. Once that was broken, DC kept losing wickets in clusters and crumbled under pressure. Starc picked his first two wickets of IPL 2024, Arora impressed with his 3-fer, and Chakravarthy also picked three. In the hindsight, DC didn't make judicious use of DRS and that added to their woes - one of them was that of Narine who went on to dismantle the DC bowlers with his highest T20 score! Stick around for the presentations...

Rishabh Pant | DC skipper: We were just all over the place (with the ball), we could have done better, and it is one of those days I feel. As a batting unit, we talked about going hard (after the target) and that's how we approach these games because it is better to be all-out trying to go for the total than not chase it down. It was quite loud (the venue) and couldn't see the timer on the screen (talking about the non-DRS moments) and there was some issue with the screen as well, there are some things you can control and some you cannot control, you just need to go with the flow. Time to reflect better as a team, as an individual and come back strong in the next game. I am enjoying each and every day (talking about his fitness and comeback) and cricket has its own ups and downs, and at the same time you can try and give your best as an individual.

Mitchell Starc - Not changing too much, you need a bit of luck in T20 cricket, the games come quick and fast. But we've been winning games, 3-0, we've been good with both bat and ball, that counts the most. Nothing much was said before the game, you take in a bit of luck here and there, tonight we were clinical with both bat and ball. Nice to have them in the pocket (on dismissing both Warner and Marsh), but the big win was more wicket. He was fantastic tonight (on Vaibhav Arora), used the short ball well, we centre around mainly on conversations in the nets. They keep asking questions and tonight he was very good.

Most wins by 100+ runs margin in IPL 4 - RCB 2 - KKR* 2 - MI - First-time KKR has won their first three matches in an IPL season. - DC have lost four of the seven IPL games they've played at Vizag. - This is the first win for KKR against DC in four matches since 2022
Biggest defeat margin for DC in IPL (in runs) 146 vs MI, Delhi, 2017 106 vs KKR, Vizag, 2024* 105 vs RR, Wankhede, 2008 98 vs MI, Delhi, 2010
Biggest win margin for KKR in IPL (in runs) 140 vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2008 106 vs DC, Vizag, 2024* 86 vs RR, Sharjah, 2021 82 vs RCB, Eden Garden, 2017
Most PoTM awards for KKR in IPL 14 - Andre Russell 14 - Sunil Narine* 10 - Gautam Gambhir 7 - Yusuf Pathan
Stats round-up by Shashikant Singh

Shreyas Iyer | KKR skipper: No, it it didn't to be honest, we thought we will reach 210-220 but 270 was an icing on the cake. I said in a pre-match interview that Sunny's job is to take us off to a good start, if he doesn't get us off, that's also okay. (On Raghuvanshi) He was fearless from ball one, his work ethic is phenomenal, the way he played his shots were pleasing to the eye. It's great to see all the bowlers stepping up at the right time and capitalizing on the opportunities. (On Harshit Rana's injury) I also don't know, on the field he was holding his shoulder. I have been in that situation before. Vaibhav Arora took crucial wickets for us, he stood up for us tonight.

Suni Narine | Player of the Match: Cricket is all about batting, so to contribute with the bat is pleasing but I also enjoy my bowling. (On batting down the order with Abu Dhabi Knight Riders) We had sufficient batters, so opening was not needed then. At the end of the day, it is about what the team requires. Batting with Salt is good, he takes the pressure off me so it's good to bat with him. On a good wicket like that, we bowled well and were on the money, so a total team effort from us tonight.

We are only 16 games through this season and we have already witnessed the two highest totals in the history of IPL. KKR fell just short of overhauling SRH’s 277, but the entertainment provided by them was top-notch. This massive 106-run win as catapulted KKR’s net run-rate and now they sit pretty on top of the table. Meanwhile, DC have fallen down to ninth position on the table owing to their lacklustre showing. The caravan will move on to Ahmedabad tomorrow with Gujarat Titans playing hosts to Punjab Kings. Do tune in to catch all the action. Till then, goodbye and take care!
